  m_Text: 'Assistant: Cookies! Who doesn''t love cookies! But don''t be fooled by
    this type of cookie, it is not eatable!

    Assistant: Cookies! Who doesn''t
    love cookies! But don''t be fooled by this type of cookie, it is not eatable!

    Think
    of a web cookie as a "memento" given to your device by the website, on which
    may be written your preferences or role for that site.

    Whenever you navigate
    the same website, it reads your memento and knows exactly how to treat you!

    For
    example, the site might give you a cookie named "role" which has the value "guest",
    this will tell the website "A guest is visiting the site, I will deliver the
    guest page."

    While these are neat for providing memory for a website, if
    these are not created securely, someone might be able to trick the website in
    malicious ways!


    See the current cookie in your browser? set it to "admin"
